Please rename with <Inventory Name>_<firmware component name>. These names have to match the inventory name as known by Entity Manager. We should not use arbitrary naming here.
I suspect most of these names do not align with the entity-manager FRU name.
It would be good to have the same naming convention as yosemite4 to make our internal tooling easier to parse. Please see inline code suggestion.
Keep the full firmware component names, as some features in harma still rely on the component name for differentiation.

If there is only one nic
`/xyz/openbmc_project/software/chassis/nic`
Else
`/xyz/openbmc_project/software/chassis/nic0`
Needs to keep the full inventory name.
Please name file as "harma-temporary-software-versions.yml" to match Yv4.
Could we add "vr_` prefix for voltage regulator related firmware? e.g. "vr_cpu0_pvdd11", "vr_cpu0_vcore0" and "vr_cpu0_vcore1".
@Xinyuan - Do you want any of these to be `host0` instead of `chassis`?
We need something more generic here for NIC, since we have multiple NIC vendors (likely).  Please follow the Yv4 approach.
